    <fr:title text="Frobenius norm">Frobenius norm</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>The entrywise Euclidean norm of a matrix — treat <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> as a long vector and take its 2-norm:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\|\mathbf {A}\|_F\ =\ \sqrt {\sum _{i,j}A_{ij}^2}\ =\ \sqrt {\langle \mathbf {A},\mathbf {A}\rangle }\ =\ \sqrt {\mathrm {tr}(\mathbf {A}^{\top }\mathbf {A})}.]]></fr:tex>
It is the norm induced by the <fr:link href="/WWMR/" title="Matrix inner product" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/WWMR/" display-uri="WWMR" type="local">matrix inner product</fr:link>, and in terms of singular values it is the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p=2]]></fr:tex> <fr:link href="/003I/" title="Schatten p-norm" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/003I/" display-uri="003I" type="local">Schatten norm</fr:link>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\|\mathbf {A}\|_F=\sqrt {\sum _i\sigma _i^2(\mathbf {A})}]]></fr:tex> — the Euclidean length of the singular-value vector, dual in that family to the <fr:link href="/3U43/" title="Spectral norm" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/3U43/" display-uri="3U43" type="local">spectral norm</fr:link> (<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p=\infty ]]></fr:tex>).</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
