                <html:p>The <fr:link href="/003G/" title="Matrix Operator Norm" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/003G/" display-uri="003G" type="local">operator norm</fr:link> of a matrix induced by the Euclidean norm on both sides, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\|\mathbf {A}\|_{2\to  2}]]></fr:tex>, usually written just <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\|\mathbf {A}\|]]></fr:tex>. It equals the largest singular value,
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\|\mathbf {A}\|\ =\ \sup _{\|\mathbf {x}\|_2\leq  1}\|\mathbf {A}\mathbf {x}\|_2\ =\ \sigma _1(\mathbf {A}),]]></fr:tex>
i.e. the most any unit vector can be stretched by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex>. As a <fr:link href="/003I/" title="Schatten p-norm" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/003I/" display-uri="003I" type="local">Schatten norm</fr:link> it is the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p=\infty ]]></fr:tex> case, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\|\mathbf {A}\|_{\mathrm {S}_\infty }=\|\sigma (\mathbf {A})\|_\infty ]]></fr:tex>, sitting opposite the <fr:link href="/4M9J/" title="Frobenius norm" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/4M9J/" display-uri="4M9J" type="local">Frobenius norm</fr:link> (<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p=2]]></fr:tex>) in that family.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
