            <fr:title text="Matrix inner product">Matrix inner product</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>The <fr:link href="/B1RI/" title="Inner Product" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/B1RI/" display-uri="B1RI" type="local">inner product</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^{m\times  n}]]></fr:tex>, obtained by treating a matrix as a long vector and summing the entrywise products:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\langle \mathbf {X},\mathbf {Z}\rangle \ :=\ \sum _{i=1}^{m}\sum _{j=1}^{n}X_{ij}Z_{ij},]]></fr:tex>
the direct generalization of the vector case <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\langle \mathbf {x},\mathbf {z}\rangle =\sum _i x_i z_i]]></fr:tex>. It is the inner product whose induced norm is the Frobenius norm, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\|\mathbf {X}\|_F=\sqrt {\langle \mathbf {X},\mathbf {X}\rangle }]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>It has a compact trace form (see <fr:link href="/PDX6/" title="Matrix trace" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/PDX6/" display-uri="PDX6" type="local">Matrix trace</fr:link>):
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\langle \mathbf {X},\mathbf {Z}\rangle \ =\ \mathrm {tr}(\mathbf {X}^{\top }\mathbf {Z})\ =\ \mathrm {tr}(\mathbf {X}\mathbf {Z}^{\top }).]]></fr:tex></html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
